  <!-- Example row of columns -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="span4">
          <h2>What</h2>
            PythonOnWheels (or short PoW) is a small and quick rapid web application generator framework for 
            <a href="http://www.python.org">python</a>.<br>
            If you want start to develop your web-application and focus on the App, 
            instead of the frameworks, you are in the right place.</p>
            <p>PythonOnWheels feels right if you do not recognize that you use it.</p>
            <p>I like to thank the brilliant ideas and implementations of <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/"> ruby on rails</a>. Patterns and theory were there, but, but rails really brought it to life. I like to keep it simple, though ;) </p>
        </div>
        <div class="span4">
          <h2>How</h2>
            <p>PythonOnWheels doesnt reinvent the wheel but is based on the brilliant frameworks out there. Namely:
            <ul>
        <li><a href="http://www.webob.org">WebOb</a> request, (response) handling. </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.sqlalchemy.org">SQLAlchemy</a> for Database abstraction, </li>
                <li><a href="http://www.makotemplates.org">Mako</a> as the Template engine </li>
                <li> <a href="http://beaker.groovie.org/">Beaker</a> for Session handling. </li>
                <li><a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/">Bootstrap</a> as base HTML/CSS Framework</li>
                <li><a href="http://jquery.com/">JQuery</a> Javascript / AJAX</li>
                <li><a href="https://github.com/nose-devs/nose/">Nose</a> Tests</li>
            </ul>
            </p>
            <p> So if you are building an app on PoW you are relying on the Python standard libs out there. </p>
            <p> PoW just brings it all together in a way that you can focus on your app instead of focusing on the frameworks. </p>
       </div>
        <div class="span4">
          <h2>...next steps</h2>
          <ol>
            <li><a class="btn" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GjQMniToYFc">Watch first-steps Screencast &raquo;</a> </li>
        <li><a class="btn btn-success" href="http://youtu.be/ylM4XKwSeRg">Watch the weblog in minutes Screencast &raquo;</a> </li>
            <li><a class="btn" href="https://github.com/pythononwheels/pow_devel/tree/beta1">Get it on github</a></li>
            <li>generate Your first <strong>model</strong>.<code>generate_model &lt;name&gt;</code></li>
            <li>generate Your first <strong>controller</strong>. <code>generate_controller &lt;name&gt;</code></li>
            <li>scaffold your views. <code>generate_scaffold &lt;name&gt;</code> </li>
            <li>start <code>simple_server.py</code>go to <strong>http://localhost:8080</strong> and enjoy. </li>
          </ol>
          <br />
          
        </div>
